<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06054m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06054m">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06054m"> 54(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> show pictures to <font color="green">[doll]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dans son d&eacute;sir de jouer un r&ocirc;le, de dominer ou de prot&eacute;ger, l&apos;enfant s&apos;emploie m&ecirc;me parfois &agrave; amuser sa poup&eacute;e. &ldquo;Un gar&ccedil;onnet de deux ans et demi demanda un jour &agrave; sa m&egrave;re: &ldquo;Veux-tu me donner tous <mark>mes livres d&apos;images pour les montrer &agrave; ma poup&eacute;e</mark>? Je ne sais pas lequel elle pr&eacute;f&eacute;rera.&rdquo; <font color="green">[In his desire to play a role, to dominate or protect, the child sometimes even amuses his doll. A two-and-a-half-year-old boy once asked his mother: &ldquo;Do you want to give me all my picture books to show them to my doll? I do not know which one she will prefer.&rdquo;]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 129</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
